{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3691064,"name":"Maya","username":"mapemaya","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mapemaya/{size}/267073_2.png","created_at":"2025-07-27T14:17:13.635Z","cooked":"<p>Hi, I’m kind of new to replay watch and have never successfully used it before.</p>
<p>I followed the documentation as closely as I could, one weird thing is that I have Windows on my computer but for some reason, while the replay watch command for mac/linux worked the one for windows didn’t (it didn’t recognize the command) but ok it ran eventually.</p>
<p>The issue is replay watch runs, a new log is created but it never finishes. Its stuck on “Replay Active” no matter what I do, and as a result it never updates the log in advantage scope (thus defeating the whole point of replay watch).</p>
<p>Regular replay works for me perfectly… Here is the relevant code</p>
<p><strong>Robot.java</strong></p>
<p><em>package frc.robot;</em></p>
<p><em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.LogFileUtil;</em><br>
<em>import org.littletonrobotics.junction.LoggedRobot;</em><br>
